Package honeyroasted.jype.type

Class AbstractType

java.lang.Object
honeyroasted.jype.type.AbstractType
All Implemented Interfaces:
Type, TypeConcrete
Direct Known Subclasses:
TypeAnd, TypeArray, TypeClass, TypeIn, TypeNone, TypeNull, TypeOr, TypeOut, TypeParameter, TypePrimitive
public abstract class AbstractType extends Object implements TypeConcrete
This is a utility class that handles common code for implementations of TypeConcrete, including holding a reference to a TypeSystem and redirecting Object.equals(Object) and Object.hashCode() to TypeConcrete.equalsExactly(TypeConcrete) and TypeConcrete.hashCodeExactly().

    • equals

      public boolean equals(Object obj)
      Tests if this TypeConcrete is equal to another TypeConcrete. Note that this method considers type equality, that is, if the types are equivalent they are considered equal regardless of their structure. If strict structural equality is needed, use TypeConcrete.equalsExactly(TypeConcrete).

      For example, this means a TypeAnd with one component type would be considered equal to its component type.

      Overrides:
      equals in class Object
      Parameters:
      obj - The object to test equality against
      Returns:
      True if this is equal to obj, false otherwise

    • hashCode

      public int hashCode()
      Generates a hashcode based for this TypeConcrete. Note that this method considers type equality, that is, two types that are equivalent will produce the same hashcode, regardless of their structure. If a strict structural hash code is needed, use TypeConcrete.hashCodeExactly().

      For example, this means a TypeAnd with one component type would produce the same hash code as its component type.

      Overrides:
      hashCode in class Object
      Returns:
      A hash code representing this type
